ìíŸ@8b1cade3ef169f134d9a0868c2c0ae3d32a112b0b59cb4fb97854303437c966c⁄	}Title: This Week in Nushell #252
Path: Nushell
Content:
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13200] fixed the 
``generate``
 command's signature
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13190] added a 
``do``
 example
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13188] suppressed column index for default 
``cal``
 output
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13182] improved table rendering in 
``help``
.
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13198] added shape_glob_interpolation to default_config.nu
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13196] fixed nu-system build on arm64 FreeBSD
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13169] fixed compilation for 
``nu_protocol::value::from_value``
 on 32-bit targets
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13089] moved most peculiar argument handling for external calls into the parser
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13061] changed the error style during tests to 
``plain``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12883] allowed plugins to report their own version and store it in the registry
.
cptpiepmatz 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13031] added derive macros for 
``FromValue``
 and 
``IntoValue``
 to ease the use of 
``Value``
s in Rust code
.
zhiburt 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13147] added vertical lines to nu-explore and fixed index/transpose issue
.
ayax79 made lots of dataframe improvements: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13193] improved performance for Polars inference
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13191] added the ability to turn on performance debugging through an env var for the Polars plugin
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13167] enabled opening JSON lines dataframes with Polars lazy JSON lines reader
.
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13180] added a system-level folder for future autoloading
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13173] updated the 
``try``
 command's help
.
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13172] updated the 
``sys users``
 signature
.
edwinjhlee 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13157] updated the README.md
.
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13113] improved commands that support range input
.
íŸ@4a3bec8bd94989dc87965ef8ccc5266c51365834e8b52ceb93b57686c49c1b28⁄*Title: This Week in Nushell #252
Path: Documentation
Content:
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1452] removed mentions of the 
``env``
 command
.
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1451] cleaned up the Imperative Language Map
 and made an 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1449] extensive Nu Map cleanup
.
dependabot
[
bot
]
 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1450] bumped braces from 3.0.2 to 3.0.3
.
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1448] upgraded the shiki syntax highlight plugin and lefthook, among others
.
maxim-uvarov 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1447] moved 
``dataframes_md-update.nu``
 file into the 
``tools``
 folder
.
íŸ@cafdad2c20db4e1893a0580ca068e28494462c2e6ad8d1dd961640e1ce3629b7⁄åTitle: This Week in Nushell #252
Path: Nu_Scripts
Content:
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/882] updated vswhere location for nu_msvs
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/881] added find_msvs custom command to the nu_msvs module
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/880] removed usage of deprecated 
``str contains --not``
.
